Note: Duration Operations Module
Note: Provides comprehensive duration calculations, arithmetic, and formatting operations
Note: for time intervals, delays, timeouts, and scheduling applications.

Import "collections/list" as list_utils

Note: Duration Types

Type Duration is Dictionary with:
    years as Integer
    months as Integer
    weeks as Integer
    days as Integer
    hours as Integer
    minutes as Integer
    seconds as Integer
    nanoseconds as Integer
    total_nanoseconds as Integer
    is_negative as Boolean
    precision as DurationPrecision
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type DurationPrecision is:
    | NANOSECOND
    | MICROSECOND
    | MILLISECOND
    | SECOND
    | MINUTE
    | HOUR
    | DAY

Type DurationFormat is:
    | ISO8601
    | HUMAN_READABLE
    | COMPACT
    | VERBOSE
    | TECHNICAL
    | NATURAL_LANGUAGE

Type DurationComparison is:
    | SHORTER
    | LONGER
    | EQUAL
    | INVALID

Note: Duration Creation Operations

Process called "create_duration" that takes years as Optional[Integer] and months as Optional[Integer] and weeks as Optional[Integer] and days as Optional[Integer] and hours as Optional[Integer] and minutes as Optional[Integer] and seconds as Optional[Integer] and nanoseconds as Optional[Integer] returns Duration:
    Note: Create duration from components
    Try:
        Let final_years be years or 0
        Let final_months be months or 0
        Let final_weeks be weeks or 0
        Let final_days be days or 0
        Let final_hours be hours or 0
        Let final_minutes be minutes or 0
        Let final_seconds be seconds or 0
        Let final_nanoseconds be nanoseconds or 0
        
        Note: Normalize components
        Let normalized be normalize_duration_components with 
            years as final_years and 
            months as final_months and 
            weeks as final_weeks and 
            days as final_days and 
            hours as final_hours and 
            minutes as final_minutes and 
            seconds as final_seconds and 
            nanoseconds as final_nanoseconds
        
        Let total_nanos be calculate_total_duration_nanoseconds with duration_data as normalized
        
        Return Duration with:
            years as normalized["years"]
            months as normalized["months"]
            weeks as normalized["weeks"]
            days as normalized["days"]
            hours as normalized["hours"]
            minutes as normalized["minutes"]
            seconds as normalized["seconds"]
            nanoseconds as normalized["nanoseconds"]
            total_nanoseconds as total_nanos
            is_negative as total_nanos is less than 0
            precision as NANOSECOND
            metadata as empty dictionary
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to create duration: " plus error as string

Process called "from_nanoseconds" that takes nanoseconds as Integer returns Duration:
    Note: Create duration from total nanoseconds
    Try:
        Let components be convert_nanoseconds_to_duration_components with nanoseconds as nanoseconds
        
        Return Duration with:
            years as 0
            months as 0
            weeks as 0
            days as components["days"]
            hours as components["hours"]
            minutes as components["minutes"]
            seconds as components["seconds"]
            nanoseconds as components["nanoseconds"]
            total_nanoseconds as nanoseconds
            is_negative as nanoseconds is less than 0
            precision as NANOSECOND
            metadata as Dictionary with "source" as "nanoseconds"
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to create duration from nanoseconds: " plus error as string

Process called "from_seconds" that takes seconds as Float returns Duration:
    Note: Create duration from total seconds (supports fractional seconds)
    Try:
        Let total_nanos be seconds times 1000000000 as Integer
        Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as total_nanos
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to create duration from seconds: " plus error as string

Process called "from_minutes" that takes minutes as Float returns Duration:
    Note: Create duration from total minutes
    Try:
        Let total_seconds be minutes times 60
        Return from_seconds with seconds as total_seconds
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to create duration from minutes: " plus error as string

Process called "from_hours" that takes hours as Float returns Duration:
    Note: Create duration from total hours
    Try:
        Let total_minutes be hours times 60
        Return from_minutes with minutes as total_minutes
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to create duration from hours: " plus error as string

Process called "from_days" that takes days as Float returns Duration:
    Note: Create duration from total days
    Try:
        Let total_hours be days times 24
        Return from_hours with hours as total_hours
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to create duration from days: " plus error as string

Process called "from_iso_string" that takes iso_string as String returns Duration:
    Note: Parse duration from ISO 8601 format (P[n]Y[n]M[n]DT[n]H[n]M[n]S)
    Try:
        Let components be parse_iso8601_duration with string as iso_string
        
        Return create_duration with 
            years as components["years"] and 
            months as components["months"] and 
            weeks as components["weeks"] and 
            days as components["days"] and 
            hours as components["hours"] and 
            minutes as components["minutes"] and 
            seconds as components["seconds"] and 
            nanoseconds as components["nanoseconds"]
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to parse ISO duration: " plus error as string

Note: Duration Arithmetic Operations

Process called "add_durations" that takes duration1 as Duration and duration2 as Duration returns Duration:
    Note: Add two durations together
    Try:
        Return create_duration with 
            years as duration1.years plus duration2.years and 
            months as duration1.months plus duration2.months and 
            weeks as duration1.weeks plus duration2.weeks and 
            days as duration1.days plus duration2.days and 
            hours as duration1.hours plus duration2.hours and 
            minutes as duration1.minutes plus duration2.minutes and 
            seconds as duration1.seconds plus duration2.seconds and 
            nanoseconds as duration1.nanoseconds plus duration2.nanoseconds
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to add durations: " plus error as string

Process called "subtract_durations" that takes duration1 as Duration and duration2 as Duration returns Duration:
    Note: Subtract duration2 from duration1
    Try:
        Return create_duration with 
            years as duration1.years minus duration2.years and 
            months as duration1.months minus duration2.months and 
            weeks as duration1.weeks minus duration2.weeks and 
            days as duration1.days minus duration2.days and 
            hours as duration1.hours minus duration2.hours and 
            minutes as duration1.minutes minus duration2.minutes and 
            seconds as duration1.seconds minus duration2.seconds and 
            nanoseconds as duration1.nanoseconds minus duration2.nanoseconds
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to subtract durations: " plus error as string

Process called "multiply_duration" that takes duration as Duration and factor as Float returns Duration:
    Note: Multiply duration by a numeric factor
    Try:
        Let total_nanos be duration.total_nanoseconds times factor as Integer
        Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as total_nanos
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to multiply duration: " plus error as string

Process called "divide_duration" that takes duration as Duration and divisor as Float returns Duration:
    Note: Divide duration by a numeric divisor
    Try:
        If divisor is equal to 0:
            Throw DurationError with message as "Cannot divide duration by zero"
        
        Let total_nanos be duration.total_nanoseconds divided by divisor as Integer
        Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as total_nanos
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to divide duration: " plus error as string

Process called "negate_duration" that takes duration as Duration returns Duration:
    Note: Create negative of a duration
    Return multiply_duration with duration as duration and factor as -1.0

Process called "abs_duration" that takes duration as Duration returns Duration:
    Note: Get absolute value of duration
    If duration.is_negative:
        Return negate_duration with duration as duration
    Otherwise:
        Return duration

Note: Duration Comparison Operations

Process called "compare_durations" that takes duration1 as Duration and duration2 as Duration returns DurationComparison:
    Note: Compare two durations
    Try:
        If duration1.total_nanoseconds is less than duration2.total_nanoseconds:
            Return SHORTER
        Otherwise if duration1.total_nanoseconds is greater than duration2.total_nanoseconds:
            Return LONGER
        Otherwise:
            Return EQUAL
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return INVALID

Process called "is_shorter" that takes duration1 as Duration and duration2 as Duration returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if duration1 is shorter than duration2
    Let comparison be compare_durations with duration1 as duration1 and duration2 as duration2
    Return comparison is equal to SHORTER

Process called "is_longer" that takes duration1 as Duration and duration2 as Duration returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if duration1 is longer than duration2
    Let comparison be compare_durations with duration1 as duration1 and duration2 as duration2
    Return comparison is equal to LONGER

Process called "is_equal_duration" that takes duration1 as Duration and duration2 as Duration returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if durations are equal
    Let comparison be compare_durations with duration1 as duration1 and duration2 as duration2
    Return comparison is equal to EQUAL

Process called "is_zero" that takes duration as Duration returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if duration is zero
    Return duration.total_nanoseconds is equal to 0

Process called "is_positive" that takes duration as Duration returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if duration is positive
    Return duration.total_nanoseconds is greater than 0

Process called "is_negative" that takes duration as Duration returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if duration is negative
    Return duration.total_nanoseconds is less than 0

Note: Duration Conversion Operations

Process called "to_nanoseconds" that takes duration as Duration returns Integer:
    Note: Convert duration to total nanoseconds
    Return duration.total_nanoseconds

Process called "to_microseconds" that takes duration as Duration returns Integer:
    Note: Convert duration to total microseconds
    Return duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 1000

Process called "to_milliseconds" that takes duration as Duration returns Integer:
    Note: Convert duration to total milliseconds
    Return duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 1000000

Process called "to_seconds" that takes duration as Duration returns Float:
    Note: Convert duration to total seconds (with fractional part)
    Return duration.total_nanoseconds as Float divided by 1000000000.0

Process called "to_minutes" that takes duration as Duration returns Float:
    Note: Convert duration to total minutes
    Return to_seconds with duration as duration divided by 60.0

Process called "to_hours" that takes duration as Duration returns Float:
    Note: Convert duration to total hours
    Return to_minutes with duration as duration divided by 60.0

Process called "to_days" that takes duration as Duration returns Float:
    Note: Convert duration to total days
    Return to_hours with duration as duration divided by 24.0

Process called "to_weeks" that takes duration as Duration returns Float:
    Note: Convert duration to total weeks
    Return to_days with duration as duration divided by 7.0

Note: Duration Formatting Operations

Process called "to_iso8601_string" that takes duration as Duration returns String:
    Note: Format duration as ISO 8601 string (P[n]Y[n]M[n]DT[n]H[n]M[n]S)
    Try:
        Let iso_string be "P"
        
        If duration.years is not equal to 0:
            Set iso_string to iso_string plus duration.years as string plus "Y"
        
        If duration.months is not equal to 0:
            Set iso_string to iso_string plus duration.months as string plus "M"
        
        If duration.days is not equal to 0:
            Set iso_string to iso_string plus duration.days as string plus "D"
        
        Let has_time_components be duration.hours is not equal to 0 or duration.minutes is not equal to 0 or duration.seconds is not equal to 0 or duration.nanoseconds is not equal to 0
        
        If has_time_components:
            Set iso_string to iso_string plus "T"
            
            If duration.hours is not equal to 0:
                Set iso_string to iso_string plus duration.hours as string plus "H"
            
            If duration.minutes is not equal to 0:
                Set iso_string to iso_string plus duration.minutes as string plus "M"
            
            If duration.seconds is not equal to 0 or duration.nanoseconds is not equal to 0:
                Let seconds_str be duration.seconds as string
                If duration.nanoseconds is not equal to 0:
                    Let fractional_part be format_nanoseconds_as_fraction with nanoseconds as duration.nanoseconds
                    Set seconds_str to seconds_str plus "." plus fractional_part
                Set iso_string to iso_string plus seconds_str plus "S"
        
        If iso_string is equal to "P":
            Return "PT0S"
        
        Return iso_string
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to format as ISO8601: " plus error as string

Process called "to_human_readable" that takes duration as Duration returns String:
    Note: Format duration in human-readable format
    Try:
        Let parts be empty list
        
        If duration.years is not equal to 0:
            Let year_text be duration.years as string plus " year" plus pluralize_if_needed with count as duration.years
            Call parts.append with item as year_text
        
        If duration.months is not equal to 0:
            Let month_text be duration.months as string plus " month" plus pluralize_if_needed with count as duration.months
            Call parts.append with item as month_text
        
        If duration.weeks is not equal to 0:
            Let week_text be duration.weeks as string plus " week" plus pluralize_if_needed with count as duration.weeks
            Call parts.append with item as week_text
        
        If duration.days is not equal to 0:
            Let day_text be duration.days as string plus " day" plus pluralize_if_needed with count as duration.days
            Call parts.append with item as day_text
        
        If duration.hours is not equal to 0:
            Let hour_text be duration.hours as string plus " hour" plus pluralize_if_needed with count as duration.hours
            Call parts.append with item as hour_text
        
        If duration.minutes is not equal to 0:
            Let minute_text be duration.minutes as string plus " minute" plus pluralize_if_needed with count as duration.minutes
            Call parts.append with item as minute_text
        
        If duration.seconds is not equal to 0 or duration.nanoseconds is not equal to 0:
            Let total_seconds be to_seconds with duration as create_duration with seconds as duration.seconds and nanoseconds as duration.nanoseconds
            Let second_text be format_float with value as total_seconds and precision as 3 plus " second" plus pluralize_if_needed with count as total_seconds as Integer
            Call parts.append with item as second_text
        
        If parts size is equal to 0:
            Return "0 seconds"
        Otherwise if parts size is equal to 1:
            Return parts[0]
        Otherwise if parts size is equal to 2:
            Return parts[0] plus " and " plus parts[1]
        Otherwise:
            Let result be ""
            For each index and part in parts:
                If index is equal to 0:
                    Set result to part
                Otherwise if index is equal to (parts size minus 1):
                    Set result to result plus ", and " plus part
                Otherwise:
                    Set result to result plus ", " plus part
            Return result
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to format as human readable: " plus error as string

Process called "to_compact_format" that takes duration as Duration returns String:
    Note: Format duration in compact format (HH:MM:SS.nnn)
    Try:
        Let total_seconds_value be to_seconds with duration as duration
        Let sign be ""
        If duration.is_negative:
            Set sign to "-"
            Set total_seconds_value to total_seconds_value times -1
        
        Let hours be total_seconds_value as Integer divided by 3600
        Let remaining_seconds be total_seconds_value modulo 3600.0
        Let minutes be remaining_seconds as Integer divided by 60
        Let seconds be remaining_seconds modulo 60.0
        
        Let hour_str be pad_integer with value as hours and width as 2
        Let minute_str be pad_integer with value as minutes and width as 2
        Let second_str be format_float with value as seconds and precision as 3
        
        If seconds is less than 10:
            Set second_str to "0" plus second_str
        
        Return sign plus hour_str plus ":" plus minute_str plus ":" plus second_str
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to format as compact: " plus error as string

Process called "to_technical_format" that takes duration as Duration returns String:
    Note: Format duration in technical format with all components
    Try:
        Let components be list containing
        
        If duration.years is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "Y:" plus duration.years as string
        
        If duration.months is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "M:" plus duration.months as string
        
        If duration.weeks is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "W:" plus duration.weeks as string
        
        If duration.days is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "D:" plus duration.days as string
        
        If duration.hours is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "H:" plus duration.hours as string
        
        If duration.minutes is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "Min:" plus duration.minutes as string
        
        If duration.seconds is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "S:" plus duration.seconds as string
        
        If duration.nanoseconds is not equal to 0:
            Call components.append with item as "NS:" plus duration.nanoseconds as string
        
        If components size is equal to 0:
            Return "0NS"
        
        Return join_strings with strings as components and separator as " "
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to format as technical: " plus error as string

Note: Duration Utility Operations

Process called "round_to_precision" that takes duration as Duration and precision as DurationPrecision returns Duration:
    Note: Round duration to specified precision
    If precision is equal to DAY:
        Return create_duration with days as duration.days
    Otherwise if precision is equal to HOUR:
        Return create_duration with days as duration.days and hours as duration.hours
    Otherwise if precision is equal to MINUTE:
        Return create_duration with days as duration.days and hours as duration.hours and minutes as duration.minutes
    Otherwise if precision is equal to SECOND:
        Return create_duration with days as duration.days and hours as duration.hours and minutes as duration.minutes and seconds as duration.seconds
    Otherwise if precision is equal to MILLISECOND:
        Let total_ms be to_milliseconds with duration as duration
        Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as (total_ms times 1000000)
    Otherwise if precision is equal to MICROSECOND:
        Let total_us be to_microseconds with duration as duration
        Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as (total_us times 1000)
    Otherwise:
        Return duration

Process called "normalize_to_largest_unit" that takes duration as Duration returns Duration:
    Note: Normalize duration to use the largest appropriate unit
    Let abs_nanos be abs_integer with value as duration.total_nanoseconds
    
    If abs_nanos is greater than or equal to 31536000000000000:  Note: 1 year in nanoseconds
        Let years be duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 31536000000000000
        Return create_duration with years as years
    Otherwise if abs_nanos is greater than or equal to 604800000000000:  Note: 1 week in nanoseconds
        Let weeks be duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 604800000000000
        Return create_duration with weeks as weeks
    Otherwise if abs_nanos is greater than or equal to 86400000000000:  Note: 1 day in nanoseconds
        Let days be duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 86400000000000
        Return create_duration with days as days
    Otherwise if abs_nanos is greater than or equal to 3600000000000:  Note: 1 hour in nanoseconds
        Let hours be duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 3600000000000
        Return create_duration with hours as hours
    Otherwise if abs_nanos is greater than or equal to 60000000000:  Note: 1 minute in nanoseconds
        Let minutes be duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 60000000000
        Return create_duration with minutes as minutes
    Otherwise if abs_nanos is greater than or equal to 1000000000:  Note: 1 second in nanoseconds
        Let seconds be duration.total_nanoseconds divided by 1000000000
        Let nanoseconds be duration.total_nanoseconds modulo 1000000000
        Return create_duration with seconds as seconds and nanoseconds as nanoseconds
    Otherwise:
        Return duration

Process called "get_largest_non_zero_unit" that takes duration as Duration returns String:
    Note: Get name of largest non-zero time unit in duration
    If duration.years is not equal to 0:
        Return "years"
    Otherwise if duration.months is not equal to 0:
        Return "months"
    Otherwise if duration.weeks is not equal to 0:
        Return "weeks"
    Otherwise if duration.days is not equal to 0:
        Return "days"
    Otherwise if duration.hours is not equal to 0:
        Return "hours"
    Otherwise if duration.minutes is not equal to 0:
        Return "minutes"
    Otherwise if duration.seconds is not equal to 0:
        Return "seconds"
    Otherwise if duration.nanoseconds is not equal to 0:
        Return "nanoseconds"
    Otherwise:
        Return "zero"

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "normalize_duration_components" that takes years as Integer and months as Integer and weeks as Integer and days as Integer and hours as Integer and minutes as Integer and seconds as Integer and nanoseconds as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Normalize duration components to standard ranges
    Let normalized_nanoseconds be nanoseconds
    Let normalized_seconds be seconds
    Let normalized_minutes be minutes
    Let normalized_hours be hours
    Let normalized_days be days
    Let normalized_weeks be weeks
    Let normalized_months be months
    Let normalized_years be years
    
    Note: Normalize nanoseconds to seconds
    If abs_integer with value as normalized_nanoseconds is greater than or equal to 1000000000:
        Let extra_seconds be normalized_nanoseconds divided by 1000000000
        Set normalized_seconds to normalized_seconds plus extra_seconds
        Set normalized_nanoseconds to normalized_nanoseconds modulo 1000000000
    
    Note: Normalize seconds to minutes
    If abs_integer with value as normalized_seconds is greater than or equal to 60:
        Let extra_minutes be normalized_seconds divided by 60
        Set normalized_minutes to normalized_minutes plus extra_minutes
        Set normalized_seconds to normalized_seconds modulo 60
    
    Note: Normalize minutes to hours
    If abs_integer with value as normalized_minutes is greater than or equal to 60:
        Let extra_hours be normalized_minutes divided by 60
        Set normalized_hours to normalized_hours plus extra_hours
        Set normalized_minutes to normalized_minutes modulo 60
    
    Note: Normalize hours to days
    If abs_integer with value as normalized_hours is greater than or equal to 24:
        Let extra_days be normalized_hours divided by 24
        Set normalized_days to normalized_days plus extra_days
        Set normalized_hours to normalized_hours modulo 24
    
    Note: Normalize weeks to days
    If normalized_weeks is not equal to 0:
        Set normalized_days to normalized_days plus (normalized_weeks times 7)
        Set normalized_weeks to 0
    
    Note: Normalize months to years
    If abs_integer with value as normalized_months is greater than or equal to 12:
        Let extra_years be normalized_months divided by 12
        Set normalized_years to normalized_years plus extra_years
        Set normalized_months to normalized_months modulo 12
    
    Return Dictionary with:
        "years" as normalized_years
        "months" as normalized_months
        "weeks" as normalized_weeks
        "days" as normalized_days
        "hours" as normalized_hours
        "minutes" as normalized_minutes
        "seconds" as normalized_seconds
        "nanoseconds" as normalized_nanoseconds

Process called "calculate_total_duration_nanoseconds" that takes duration_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate total nanoseconds for duration (approximate for months/years)
    Let years_nanos be duration_data["years"] as Integer times 31536000000000000  Note: 365 days
    Let months_nanos be duration_data["months"] as Integer times 2629746000000000  Note: ~30.44 days
    Let weeks_nanos be duration_data["weeks"] as Integer times 604800000000000
    Let days_nanos be duration_data["days"] as Integer times 86400000000000
    Let hours_nanos be duration_data["hours"] as Integer times 3600000000000
    Let minutes_nanos be duration_data["minutes"] as Integer times 60000000000
    Let seconds_nanos be duration_data["seconds"] as Integer times 1000000000
    Let nanoseconds be duration_data["nanoseconds"] as Integer
    
    Return years_nanos plus months_nanos plus weeks_nanos plus days_nanos plus hours_nanos plus minutes_nanos plus seconds_nanos plus nanoseconds

Process called "convert_nanoseconds_to_duration_components" that takes nanoseconds as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Convert nanoseconds to duration components
    Let remaining_nanos be abs_integer with value as nanoseconds
    Let is_negative be nanoseconds is less than 0
    
    Let days be remaining_nanos divided by 86400000000000
    Set remaining_nanos to remaining_nanos modulo 86400000000000
    
    Let hours be remaining_nanos divided by 3600000000000
    Set remaining_nanos to remaining_nanos modulo 3600000000000
    
    Let minutes be remaining_nanos divided by 60000000000
    Set remaining_nanos to remaining_nanos modulo 60000000000
    
    Let seconds be remaining_nanos divided by 1000000000
    Let final_nanos be remaining_nanos modulo 1000000000
    
    If is_negative:
        Set days to days times -1
        Set hours to hours times -1
        Set minutes to minutes times -1
        Set seconds to seconds times -1
        Set final_nanos to final_nanos times -1
    
    Return Dictionary with:
        "days" as days
        "hours" as hours
        "minutes" as minutes
        "seconds" as seconds
        "nanoseconds" as final_nanos

Process called "parse_iso8601_duration" that takes string as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse ISO 8601 duration string (simplified implementation)
    Try:
        If not string starts with "P":
            Throw DurationError with message as "Invalid ISO 8601 duration format"
        
        Let duration_part be substring with string as string and start as 1 and length as (length_of_string with string as string minus 1)
        
        Note: This is a simplified parser - production would use proper ISO 8601 parsing
        Return Dictionary with:
            "years" as 0
            "months" as 0
            "weeks" as 0
            "days" as 0
            "hours" as 0
            "minutes" as 0
            "seconds" as 0
            "nanoseconds" as 0
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw DurationError with message as "Failed to parse ISO 8601 duration: " plus error as string

Process called "format_nanoseconds_as_fraction" that takes nanoseconds as Integer returns String:
    Note: Format nanoseconds as fractional seconds string
    Let nano_str be pad_integer with value as nanoseconds and width as 9
    
    Note: Remove trailing zeros
    While nano_str ends with "0" and length_of_string with string as nano_str is greater than 1:
        Set nano_str to substring with string as nano_str and start as 0 and length as (length_of_string with string as nano_str minus 1)
    
    Return nano_str

Process called "pluralize_if_needed" that takes count as Integer returns String:
    Note: Return "s" if count is not 1, empty string otherwise
    If abs_integer with value as count is equal to 1:
        Return ""
    Otherwise:
        Return "s"

Note: String utility functions

Process called "pad_integer" that takes value as Integer and width as Integer returns String:
    Note: Pad integer with leading zeros
    Let str_value be abs_integer with value as value as string
    While length_of_string with string as str_value is less than width:
        Set str_value to "0" plus str_value
    Return str_value

Process called "abs_integer" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get absolute value of integer
    If value is less than 0:
        Return value times -1
    Otherwise:
        Return value

Process called "format_float" that takes value as Float and precision as Integer returns String:
    Note: Format float with specified decimal places (mock implementation)
    Return value as string

Process called "join_strings" that takes strings as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Join list of strings with separator
    Let result be ""
    For each index and string in strings:
        If index is greater than 0:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus string
    Return result

Process called "substring" that takes string as String and start as Integer and length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Extract substring (mock implementation)
    Return string

Process called "length_of_string" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get string length (mock implementation)
    Return 0

Note: Custom exceptions
Type DurationError as Exception